      "name": "Synthesis of prior hemolysis modelling studies — consolidated credibility basis",
      "description": "This node represents a synthesis of multiple prior peer-reviewed studies on CFD-based hemolysis prediction in rotary blood pumps, compiled to provide consolidated credibility evidence across turbulence model choices, mesh strategies, and experimental comparators. The synthesis draws on Goubergrits & Affeld (2004), Grigioni et al. (2005), Taskin et al. (2012), and Fraser et al. (2012), covering a combined experimental dataset of over 40 pump operating conditions. It is treated as an established evidentiary foundation for the MRL-5 assessment. No individual upstream derivation edge is encoded because the synthesis predates the current provenance schema adoption; the compilers assumed its foundational status would be self-evident from the literature citations embedded in the rationale narrative. This assumption is incorrect from a machine-readable provenance standpoint — the node has no prov:wasDerivedFrom, no prov:wasGeneratedBy, and no prov:used link, and uofa:isFoundationalEvidence is not set to true, creating a dead-end orphan in the provenance chain."
